STATE Police in Lejweleputswa district are looking for suspect/s following the
brutal death of a couple. The
couple in their early 50s were found with bullet wounds on their heads  on the side of the road. Police
spokeswoman Sergeant Sinah Mpakane said in a statement that On Thursday, 07July
2022 between 15:00 and 16:00 police received information of a shooting incident
on the R64 road between Dealesville and Boshoff road. "On
arrival they found a White Triber sedan parked on the side of the road. The car
was travelling from Dealesville to Boshoff. Two people were found dead who were
later identified as Lucas Moleme (52) and his wife Lyntjie Moleme
(50)." READ: Couple dies in shack fire! Mpakane
said a male victim was lying next to a car with a gunshot wound on the head and
a woman still in a sitting position in the car. "She
was also having a gunshot wound on the head. Victims were both staying in
Boshoff and are owners of Kgakgamatso Mortuary. No one is arrested. The motive
of the killing is unknown." Mphakane
pleaded that annyone with information that can lead to the arrest of suspect/s
is requested to contact investigating officer W/O Nel of Thabong Detectives on
082 806 8432. 